Got it, skipping the build. Here's what I added:

## What changed

Added a `jq` patch in `createAgent` (step 5, before gateway restart) that sets:

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "subagents": {
        "maxSpawnDepth": 2,
        "allowAgents": ["*"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

This runs once when the first agent is deployed. It tells the main agent (the one connected to Telegram) that it's allowed to delegate tasks to any named agent.

## How it works from Telegram

After deploying e.g. "Marketing Agent" from the dashboard, the user can message the Telegram bot:

```
Use the marketing agent to analyze our competitors
```

The main agent sees the available named agents, spawns `marketing` as a sub-agent, the marketing agent does the work with its own skills/system prompt, and announces the result back — all within the same Telegram chat.

The only thing needed is that this `jq` patch runs at least once. It's idempotent — running it again on subsequent deploys just re-sets the same values.

